6 RETENTION PAY FOR STATE EMPLOYEES
7 SECTION 2.3.(a) All references to "longevity" pay in Chapter 126 of the General
8 Statutes shall be replaced with "retention" pay.
9 SECTION 2.3.(b) The amount of retention pay provided to employees who are
10 full-time or over half-time and have a permanent, time-limited, or probationary appointment and
11 who are in pay status for one-half of the regularly scheduled workdays and holidays in a pay
12 period shall be increased to the following amounts:
13 Years of Total Service Retention Pay Percentage
14 2 but less than 5 years 1.0%
15 5 but less than 10 years 1.5%
16 10 but less than 15 years 2.0%
17 15 but less than 20 years 2.5%
18 20 but less than 25 years 3.5%
19 25 or more years 4.5%
20
21 RETENTION BONUS AWARDED FOR FISCAL YEAR
22 SECTION 2.4.(a) Any person (i) whose salary is set by Section 1 of this act or this
23 Part, pursuant to the North Carolina Human Resources Act, or as otherwise authorized in this act
24 and (ii) who is continuously employed by the State or a public school unit from July 1, 2025, to
25 October 31, 2025, shall be awarded a retention bonus for the 2025-2026 fiscal year in the amount
26 of five hundred dollars ($500.00), payable during the month of November 2025. For otherwise
27 eligible local education employees, eligibility for the bonus shall be measured beginning not on
28 July 1, 2025, but on the first day when staff report for the 2025-2026 school year.
29 SECTION 2.4.(b) Any person (i) whose salary is set by Section 1 of this act or this
30 Part, pursuant to the North Carolina Human Resources Act, or as otherwise authorized in this act
31 and (ii) who is continuously employed by the State or a public school unit from November 1,
32 2025, to March 31, 2026, shall be awarded an additional retention bonus for the 2025-2026 fiscal
33 year in the amount of five hundred dollars ($500.00), payable during the month of April 2026.
34 SECTION 2.4.(c) Employers of State employees and local education employees
35 shall provide an additional retention bonus of two hundred fifty dollars ($250.00), payable
36 during the month of November 2025, to all permanent full-time State employees and local
37 education employees who are continuously employed by the State or a public school unit from
38 July 1, 2025, to October 31, 2025, and who earn an annual salary that does not exceed
39 seventy-five thousand dollars ($75,000).
40 SECTION 2.4.(d) Employers of State employees and local education employees
41 shall provide an additional retention bonus of two hundred fifty dollars ($250.00), payable
42 during the month of April 2026, to all permanent full-time State employees and local education
43 employees who are employed by the State or a public school unit from November 1, 2025, to
44 March 31, 2026, and who earn an annual salary that does not exceed seventy-five thousand
45 dollars ($75,000).
46 SECTION 2.4.(e) The funds appropriated for retention bonuses in excess of the
47 amounts required to implement these bonuses shall revert and not be credited to the Pay Plan
48 Reserve.
49 SECTION 2.4.(f) Notwithstanding G.S. 135-1(7a), the compensation bonuses
50 awarded by this section are not compensation under Article 1 of Chapter 135 of the General
51 Statutes, the Teachers' and State Employees' Retirement System.
