42 (2) For the 2026-2027 fiscal year, shall be paid effective on July 1, 2026, and do
43 not apply to persons separated from service due to resignation, dismissal,
44 reduction in force, death, or retirement or whose last workday is prior to June
45 30, 2026.
46 SECTION 2.11.(b) The Director of the Budget is granted flexibility to administer
47 the compensation increases enacted by this act.
48 SECTION 2.11.(c) The State employer contribution rates enacted by this act for
49 retirement and related benefits may be deemed by the Director of the Budget for administrative
50 purposes to become effective after July 1 of the applicable fiscal year to provide flexibility in the
51 collection and reconciliation of salary-related contributions as required by law, provided the
